Subject: Re: [T2] Check Air/Fuel Mixture Using Oxygen Sensor?

On 8/12/04 7:44 AM, "Timothy Woenker" <multipang(-at-)kconline.com> wrote:

> Has anyone 
> successfully used the output ffrom  the oxygen sensor to check air/fuel
> mixture ratio?

You can use a VOM but it needs to be of Fluke caliber (1mV accuracy) and
needs a min/max mode to capture the values as the voltages swing up and down
the hystersis curve that the O2 sensor outputs.

The AFR gauges have an amplification circuit built in to reach the output.

